From: Vincenzo <vincenzo@vortex86-builder>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 15:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix gnulib nodiscard attribute for C23 compat

GCC 15+ defaults to -std=c23, where [[nodiscard]] is a standard
attribute. The gnulib code in m4 1.4.19 tries to use [[__nodiscard__]]
when __STDC_VERSION__ >= 201710L, but the attribute placement in
some headers (e.g., gl_oset.h) is incompatible with C23's stricter
attribute parsing rules, causing:

  gl_oset.h:275: error: expected identifier or '(' before 'int'

Fix by disabling the [[nodiscard]] path so that the fallback
__attribute__((__warn_unused_result__)) is used instead.

Signed-off-by: Vincenzo <vincenzo@vortex86-builder>

diff --git a/lib/config.hin b/lib/config.hin
index 4abeaac..b8c7e3c 100644
--- a/lib/config.hin
+++ b/lib/config.hin
@@ -2586,7 +2586,7 @@
 # define _GL_ATTRIBUTE_MAYBE_UNUSED
 #endif
 
-#if 201710L < __STDC_VERSION__
+#if 0 /* disabled for C23 compat */
 # define _GL_ATTRIBUTE_NODISCARD [[__nodiscard__]]
 #elif _GL_HAS_ATTRIBUTE (warn_unused_result)
 # define _GL_ATTRIBUTE_NODISCARD __attribute__ ((__warn_unused_result__))
